1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 37-17.1 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to criminal history record checks by the department of emergency
3 services; and to amend and reenact subdivision nn of subsection 2 of section 12-60-24 of the
4 North Dakota Century Code, relating to criminal history record checks by the department of
5 emergency services.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
7 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 37-17.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
8 and enacted as follows:
9 Criminal history record checks.
10 The department of emergency services may require a final applicant for a job opening or a
11 current employee who works with the department of emergency services to submit to a
12 statewide and nationwide criminal history record check. The nationwide criminal history record
13 check must be conducted in the manner provided by section 12 - 60 - 24 .
14 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subdivision nn of subsection 2 of section 12-60-24 of the North
15 Dakota Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
16 nn. The office of the adjutant general for a final applicant for a job opening or current
17 employees and volunteers working with the office of the adjutant general,
18 including the recruiting and retention, sexual assault, and youth programs, or with
19 the department of emergency services.
